      %h2 The GGI Data Portal
    %p.c9.c2.c10
      %span
    %p.c9.c2
      %span.c7 The GGI Data Portal enables scientists to identify where biodiversity genomic knowledge exists for each family of living organisms, and allows them to focus new knowledge-building efforts.  Core sources of knowledge include Biodiversity Heritage Library pages (BHL), Barcode of Life Records (BOLD), Encyclopedia of Life (EOL) rich pages, Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF) records, GenBank sequences, and Global Genome Biodiversity Network (GGBN) records.  
