      %h2 Taxonomy
    %p.c9.c2.c10
      %span.c1
    %p.c9.c2
      %span.c1.c8 The GGI Data Portal Taxonomy is based on the list of Families of Living Organisms (FALO) compiled by Ruggiero (2014) as an extension of a seven-kingdom classification of life in Ruggiero et al. (in prep 2014).  The latter work is the result of an experts panel representing the major taxonomic disciplines convened to review, revise, and update the existing incomplete Catalogue of Life (CoL) hierarchy down to order.  This new classification is based on a consensus view among the authors, accommodating taxonomic choices and practical compromises among diverse opinions, usages and conflicting evidence of the boundaries between ranks and some major taxa, including kingdoms.
