      %h2 Features
    %p.c2
      %b Search
      %span.c0  functions as an autocomplete.  The user starts typing the beginning of a family name and is presented with a list of matching names from the taxonomy tree to choose from.  Users can select a name and the node in the taxonomy tree is selected.
    %p.c2
      %b Taxonomy tree
      %span.c0 contains FALO classification from ranks superkingdom to family. This tree is 1) expandable and collapsible, 2) scrollable with fixed dimensions and 3) lists nodes alphabetically. Tree nodes are selectable.  When a node is selected the source, value, score data and taxonomic information changes.  Each node has a unique URL.  
